  "title": "Camp Mystic Files for Bankruptcy After 28 Died in the Texas Flood",
  "script": "Who's paying for this? Camp Mystic — an all-girls Christian summer camp on the Guadalupe River in the Texas Hill Country — filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy last Wednesday. Nearly a year after catastrophic floods swept through on July 4th, 2025, killing 25 campers aged 8 to 10, two teenage counselors, and the camp's longtime director. 28 people dead. Investigators found the camp had no written emergency plan that met state requirements. They delayed evacuation despite ample warning. The camp had planned to reopen this summer for its 100th anniversary. Victim families said no. Now Camp Mystic owes somewhere between $10 million and $50 million. Who in the Texas Hill Country saw those floods coming — except the people in charge?",
